                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2037: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Nanking</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 13, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. For the Minister: Legation’s 740, October 10 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>], 8
                    a.m. In view of your 748, October 12, 8 p.m., you are authorized in reply to
                    inform the Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs that the American Government is
                    expecting momentarily to receive from American official sources a full report
                    with regard to the incident at Chinchow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
